text: Reiner of Meissen, also noted as Rainer, Reginbert, Rogmer or Reinbert (died 1066), was Bishop of Meissen from 1065 to 1066. He was consecrated by Werner of Steusslingen (or Steutzlingen), Archbishop of Magdeburg.Eduard Machatschek: Geschichte der Bischöfe des Hochstiftes Meissen in chronologischer Reihenfolge (...), pp. 60-62.
